node.text: Okay, this was one of the funnest moments I’ve ever had in my life. This is a completely original song and video, and I felt “Like a Boss”! This movie is a must-see. Reserve tickets 🎟️ now to see it FIRST at Girls’ Night Out advance screenings tomorrow, in theatres everywhere Friday. #ad

node.text:
Let's get personal. A lot of you have been asking me about baby #2 and what I turned to for birth control after having my daughter, Ocean. As many of you know, I suffer from migraines, so using birth control with hormones was absolutely not an option for me. 
 
I had heard about @naturalcycles — the first FDA cleared birth control app — through a friend who has used it for years. Natural Cycles is 100% natural & empowers women by teaching them about what’s going on in their bodies naturally. It’s hard to believe that even after going through pregnancy, there’s so much I still have to learn about my body.
 
Of course, there’s no one size fits all for birth control so it’s important to understand what will work for you, so here’s how it works: 
 
•There are only certain days of the month you are fertile and can get pregnant. The app is powered by an algorithm that is able to identify your daily fertility status based on your basal body temperature (BBT).
•First thing in the morning, you measure your BBT with an NC thermometer & input it into the app. NC then gives you a red or green day. Green day = not fertile and can do your thing. Red day = fertile and can still do your thing...but you need to use protection.

When used perfectly, Natural Cycles is 98% effective. Perfect use means not having unprotected sex on red days. Natural Cycles is 93% effective with typical use. It can also help plan pregnancy faster if that’s something you want. Just switch from NC° Birth Control to NC° Plan Pregnancy right in the app.

I’m thankful to be working with a brand that works for me and my body. If you feel that Natural Cycles may be the best choice for you, like I feel it is for me, you can get 20% off your annual subscription + a free thermometer with promo code “LALAKENT” on NaturalCycles.com 

Users must be over the age of 18 and it does not protect against STIs (only barrier methods, such as condoms, prevent STIs)
#naturalcycles #ad 

p.s. for the new mamas out there: If you watch my stories you know I’m still breastfeeding. Every woman is different post pregnancy, but Natural Cycles does recommend getting started once you’ve gotten your first period!

node.text: Ocean, Gigi (O’s grandmama) and I took a trip to Newport Beach for a few days to see our family friends. I had to post this sweet moment of Ocean and her best friend Hazel. Hazel’s mama, Olivia, and I have been best friends for 30 years (yes, our entire lives), and our mama’s have been the same since Jr. High- 3 generations. Liv and I have pictures together as babies we always look back on, and now our girls will have the same. Kisses to that 😘
